<p>This is what I have so far, albeit scaled down. I want the user to click on pre-defined values, as in the first two divs, or click on "Input Custom Value" which brings focus to the #enter_custom input where they can enter their own value. The user will add each value option to the total by clicking "Add to Total" after highlighting either predefined value or entering a custom value. Hope that much makes sense.</p>  <p>I cannot for the life of me get the user defined input value to add to the total. Not sure if I need to remove focus before it can be added. I've tried that (and many more failures), but perhaps I was using the wrong approach -- blur() -- or, perhaps I'm on the wrong track altogether. Total displays as NaN for everything I've tried. Help will be much appreciated. </p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>$(document).ready(function() {   var $total = 0;   $('#total').html($total);    $('.activate').click(function() {     $(this).addClass('selected');     $(this).siblings().removeClass('selected');      var $value = $(this).find('input').val();     var $totalChanger = parseInt($value, 10);      $('#add').click(function() {       $('#total').html($total = $total + $totalChanger);       $('div').removeClass('selected');       $('#enter_custom').val('');       $totalChanger = 0;     }); /* $('#correct').click(function(){ */      $('#trigger_custom').click(function() {       if ($total &lt;= 0) {         alert("You lose!");       } else {         $('#enter_custom').focus();       }     }); /* $('#trigger_custom').click(function(){ */    }); /* $('.activate').click(function(){ */  }); /* $(document).ready(function(){ */</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>div {   width: 170px;   margin: 0 10px 20px 10px;   border: thin solid #111;   padding: 20px;   text-align: center;   cursor: pointer; } .selection:ho